      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Here are the results for your query:\n\n## \"Adaptive Chameleon or Stubborn Sloth: Revealing the Behavior of Large Language Models in Knowledge Conflicts\"\n\n**Authors:** "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Jian Xie (Fudan University), Kai Zhang (The Ohio State University), Jiangjie Chen (Fudan University), Renze Lou (The Pennsylvania State University), and Yu Su (The Ohio State University)."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n**Venue:** "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Published as part of the International Conference on Learning Representations 2024 (ICLR 2024)."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": " "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "It received a **Spotlight** designation at ICLR 2024."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n**Paper Links:**\n- **arXiv:** https://arxiv.org/abs/2305.13300\n- **OpenReview:** https://openreview.net/forum?id=auKAUJZMO6\n- **GitHub:** https://github.com/OSU-NLP-Group/LLM-Knowledge-Conflict\n\n### Summary\n\n"
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Tool augmentation (including retrieval augmentation) has emerged as a promising solution for addressing the limitations of LLMs' static parametric memory."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": " "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "However, how receptive are LLMs to such external evidence, especially when the evidence conflicts with their parametric memory?"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n"
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The authors present the first comprehensive and controlled investigation into the behavior of LLMs when encountering knowledge conflicts, proposing a systematic framework to elicit high-quality parametric memory from LLMs and construct the corresponding counter-memory, enabling a series of controlled experiments."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n### Key Findings\n\n"
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The investigation reveals seemingly contradicting behaviors of LLMs. On the one hand, different from prior wisdom, LLMs can be highly receptive to external evidence even when it conflicts with their parametric memory, given that the external evidence is coherent and convincing."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n"
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "On the other hand, LLMs also demonstrate a strong confirmation bias when the external evidence contains some information that is consistent with their parametric memory, despite being presented with conflicting evidence at the same time."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n"
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "These results pose important implications that are worth careful consideration for the further development and deployment of tool- and retrieval-augmented LLMs."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n### TL;DR\n\n"
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "This paper explores LLMs' responses to knowledge conflicts: are they Adaptive Chameleons, open to external evidence, or Stubborn Sloths, holding onto parametric memory?"
      }
    ],
